preambule.al:
Being desirous of regulating the relationship
between the two countries in the field of social security;
and

prevent double coverage and to avoid non-coverage
under the social security systems of both countries for persons moving
between or working in their respective territories;

li.al:
in relation to the
Netherlands, the territory of the Kingdom of the Netherlands in
Europe;

in relation to the
Netherlands, the Minister of Social Affairs and
Employment;

“Employee” means a person who is
employed by an employer as well as any person who is deemed equivalent
to an employed person by the applicable legislation;

“Benefit” means any pension or
benefit in cash, including any supplements or increases applicable
under the legislation specified in Article 2;

“Member of the family” means any
person defined or recognized as such by the applicable
legislation;

sickness (including the
scheme concerning the liability of the employer and benefit in
kind);

if
such recognition is contrary to public policy in the Contracting State
in which recognition is sought;

as
regards old age and survivors’ pension for employed persons:
Employees’ Provident Fund Organization;

as regards the Permanent Total Disability pension
for employed persons: Employees’ Provident Fund Organization,
and

for the application of Part II of the Agreement:
Sociale verzekeringsbank (Social Insurance Bank),
Amstelveen.

as
regards old age and survivors’ pension for employed persons:
Employees’ Provident Fund Organization;

as regards the Permanent Total Disability pension
for employed persons: Employees’ Provident Fund Organization;
and

for the application of Part II of the Agreement:
Sociale verzekeringsbank, (Social Insurance Bank),
Amstelveen.

preambule.al:
Geleid door de wens de betrekkingen tussen
beide landen op het gebied van sociale zekerheid te regelen;
en

li.al:
wat Nederland betreft, het grondgebied van het
Koninkrijk der Nederlanden in
Europa;

wat Nederland betreft, een
persoon met de Nederlandse
nationaliteit;

wat Nederland betreft, de
minister van Sociale Zaken en
Werkgelegenheid;

„wetgeving”
de wet- en regelgeving omschreven in artikel
2;

ziekte (met inbegrip van de regeling inzake de
aansprakelijkheid van een werkgever en uitkeringen in
natura);

indien
deze erkenning in strijd is met de openbare orde in de verdragsluitende
staat waarin erkenning wordt beoogd;

wat betreft arbeidsongeschiktheidsuitkeringen:
het Uitvoeringsinstituut werknemersverzekeringen, Amsterdam;
